The paper deals with the problem of detecting Hardware Trojans, which is a subfield of hardware security. Therefore, cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves Automatic Test Pattern Generation (ATPG) and Boolean Satisfiability (SAT) solvers, which are techniques used in the field of computer architecture and design, making cs.AR (Architecture) a likely category as well. The paper also discusses the scalability issues in Trojan detection, which is a common problem in software engineering, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of simulation results, which is a common technique in the field of digital circuits, making cs.DC (Digital Circuits) a possible category.
